anything_else.value: I am highly passionate about educating others to be healthy. The forum by which I do that now is limited and I am looking for guidance in successfully taking that next leap towards the inevitable and exciting mix of fitness, health, business, and technology.

code_experience.value:
I have been working on codecademy for the past few weeks, and "played" around with HTML for the first time about 8 years ago (though it never went beyond personal interest).

I want to learn to code to give myself a competitive advantage in my field. My professional backgrounds are in investment management and fitness (yes - quite diverse!) and I feel coding skills will help me stand out.

two_years.value:
In 3 years, I would like to be well on my way to creating a location independent work life. 

I would like to have created and marketed a tool/product/service that companies can use to successfully engage employees in the long term in corporate settings. My second goal is to create tools for consumers which truly assist them in moving towards better health by effecting true behaviour change.

interests.value:
I have worked in the fitness industry for the past 6 years and incorporated web technology into my business from the start (creating a tribe of clients via my online newsletters; providing online education via my member site). To be successful in this industry (and all service industries), we must engage in proven business practice and embrace technology. 

I created my site using Wordpress, and expanded it to include e-commerce capabilities and a membership portal. It proved successful and expanded my thoughts of what a "fitness trainer" could do for his or her clients outside of the traditional gym one-on-one setting.

Finally, I still kick myself for not pursuing computer science as an undergrad over 20 years ago! Finding ways to use technology in all of my professional endeavors has proven fruitful, and I am looking forward to taking my knowledge and curiosity to the next level.

why_attend.value: I am attracted to the possibility of working with like-minded individuals excited about bringing forward their ideas and creating something new. The mentoring and camaraderie are highly appealing as is the ability to get valuable business feedback while actually creating a product.

anything_else.value: I like long walks on the beach, and Thai food...<But, Seriously>I am a transplant to Cape Breton, or what locals refer to as a "Cape Bretoner by Choice." I'm proud of that fact as I've grown very fond of the island, its people and potential. In order to elevate some of the talent, ideas, insight and innovation in Cape Breton, I recently produced TEDxCapeBreton (with a small army of dedicated volunteers & partners). Our aim was to help reconcile any misconceptions about the region and to share new perspectives with the world via the TED/TEDx platform and Livestream. To learn more about that project, please visit http://www.tedxcapebreton.com. To learn more about other community initiatives and my professional background, please peruse http://www.linkedin.com/in/hvoyles. To learn more about me, personally, please view the public information in the "Details About You" section on Facebook at https://www.facebook.com/heathermvoyles2/about?section=bio. Thank you for your consideration.

code_experience.value: A decade ago, I worked for a dot-com (mdnetlink.com), which provided database generated and custom websites with physician approved content for health associations, doctors and specialists. The company was owned by a network of physicians, and our team was quite lean. As part of a small business, "all hands on deck" was the prevailing mentality. As a result, a ridiculously talented intern whop now codes for Boeing taught me HTML when it became impossible to decipher and edit site content in Dreamweaver's automatically generated (messy) code in his absence. While I am NO coding expert, I have a basic understanding of HTML, but I'm certainly rusty and could use practice. I've always enjoyed learning new languages. Interacting with codeacademy.com has been  fun.

two_years.value: I see myself learning, failing, adapting and then launching a new start-up venture, or collaborating with others to launch and market a new concept with export potential.

interests.value: Everything. They are my passion, my muse. They excite & delight me, stir & motivate me, and in some cases perplex & frustrate me. They inspire me to wake up every morning, and in many cases, they keep me up at night as new ideas, possibilities and questions bully my shut-eye. It is my dream to intersect the two in an entrepreneurial, socially responsible venture than enhances lives and the community.

why_attend.value: In one word: "Immersion." In many words: I'm a technology obsessed business professional with an entrepreneurial spirit. I've always been interested in launching a start-up venture, and "someday" is now. I've been toying around with a few ideas for the past year, but I'm still gathering information and learning methods for pulling it all together. I've been responsible for developing and marketing (tangible consumer) products for other companies for some time now. It would be such a gift to have a stronger technical foundation to help pull all my interests and ideas together and to better understand what developing a start-up might entail by collaborating with others who have made their vision a reality (or failed, which is equally important). Given my nature, I must admit, I'm also intrigued by what I know about the program format. It seems less formulaic and more experientially based. Leadership's commitment to an equitable male to female student ratio is also alluring and commendable.

anything_else.value: I have a degree in Economics, an IT diploma and I have completed eight courses in International Business.  I have lived in Asia for five years so I have insights business models and opportunities different from our own.

code_experience.value: I have a diploma in Applied Information Technology (2001) however, my hard programming skills are almost non-existent.

two_years.value: Working for myself!

interests.value: The ability to reach distant consumers through the click of a mouse.

why_attend.value: I need coding knowledge to put my thoughts into action.  I also need to learn creative ways to bring a product or idea to market.

anything_else.value: I recently quit my job to pursue my own startup ideas. The timing is absolutely perfect...and I'm female :)

code_experience.value: Extensive. I have a degree in Computer Science from Dalhousie University and have spent the last 5 years in industry in software engineering.

two_years.value: I no longer set goals. See my post on LinkedIn for the reason why: http://www.linkedin.com/today/post/article/20140721165535-37776714-stop-setting-goals-already . My 'Destination' is to feel alive, free, and secure (reference to an exercise in Top Down Living Lesson 1: http://www.needster.com/lesson1.html). That's where I'll be in 1 year. Three years? I'm okay not knowing.

interests.value: I have oodles of startup ideas. The skill set I lack is the business acumen. I have been enrolled in Business at Acadia and dropped out after a month. I also started a self-directed virtual MBA using the materials from MIT OpenCourseWare (from that info I put together this Virtual MBA idea http://virtualmbaorg.appspot.com). Business courses bore me to tears. I would love to learn the industry in an innovative and exciting way. Fingers crossed this platform will do that!

why_attend.value: I love learning for the sake of learning.

anything_else.value: When I heard about UIT at the StartUpCapeBreton event I was surprised and interested with the idea of this program since the whole idea behind UIT Cape Breton caught my attention a few years ago (that is building a technology based start-up). I know that if I am accepted I will be extremely hard working and incredibly passionate towards every idea which I choose to foster. I hope I can use my creative capacity and strong leadership to help launch a highly successful economic change for Cape Breton. Thank you very much for your consideration and for reading!   James

code_experience.value: I have previous experience in coding in both high school and university. In high school I took a multimedia class which introduced me to working on web designing using some HTML code and adobe fireworks to create an interactive website. I have also taken a introduction to C++ class at CBU. Personally, I see coding just as empowering and applicable as reading or writing since while you are learning to code you can practice, use, and create with it. Another great aspect of coding is it's availability; you can simply look up what you want to know and learn it without spending lots of money through universities to teach you code. However the strategies, applications to business, and business 'tech'niques surrounding technology start-ups is something I can hopefully learn more about through UIT before I embark on a business journey.

two_years.value: In 3 years time I see myself furthering my education in a post-secondary institution. I would still like to see myself sampling new ideas learning new concepts, and applying what I am learning since I know that if I wish to empower myself, then education is the best way to achieve that goal. The media too often covers 'college dropout start-ups' and their success, but I feel that if I want to start a successful business I need to educate myself as well to help myself and my business. At the same time, when I pursue a business idea, I want to be so sure of myself and my intentions so that I know that I am passionate enough about the idea to put my full-fledged effort into fostering it's success.

interests.value: What interests me the most about business and technology is the entire concept of having an original idea, the will to start building working on your idea and making it a reality in which an arbitrary number of people can access it. Whether your idea is recognized for solving a modern issue or receives recognition through people’s positive response towards it, being able to share your idea and have individuals, government, businesses and communities benefit from it either through direct usage, employment, experience, or recognition can help people across the globe and in your community. The journey of creating a company around a few ideas mixed in with the proper experience, passion, know-how, development, and people is a journey I definitely wish to experience and is one I hope will be involved in.

why_attend.value: Since I've enrolled at CBU I've been thinking about my future career and the type of job I would want when I finish university. I am an engineering student and have always been told that job opportunities for engineers are abundant compared to other professions, I've always admired great ideas which help create great jobs, not just for engineers, but for all professions. Before I enrolled at CBU, I've wanted to create jobs for others in some way; when I heard about UIT at StartUpCapeBreton last month I thought that this program would be a perfect way to learn how to build a business from an idea while being able to bring that idea into fruition. Spearheading the economic challenges not just in Cape Breton, but in Canada through tech entrepreneurship is a highly appealing way to engage new entrepreneurs such as myself because personally, the idea of becoming an entrepreneur so that I can equip others with opportunity, employment,while developing and leading a new business is a very enticing opportunity for me.

anything_else.value: In the summer 2013 I was among the first canadians to do a hackathon on Google Glass. Creating the first MP3 player on the device, even before Google themselves had a first party music app. http://www.betakit.com/four-first-of-their-kind-apps-created-at-canadian-google-glass-hackathon/In that year I also invited to become a Google Glass Explorer. Receiving my unit in November. Since then I've been trying to educate myself and others on how the future of wearables will be. I also built a helicopter that flies you whiskey with the tap of your phone.http://thebestwebsiteintheworld.ca/?tag=AR.DroneWe are wearables meetup where I'll be on a panel this month. http://www.meetup.com/Wearable-Wednesday-Toronto/events/199119852/

code_experience.value: Currently I work as a web developer. My skills in the industry are up there but if I had to rank myself on the 10,000 hours rule I'd say I am roughly 4,000 hours in. HTML, CSS, JavaScript, PHP, Wordpress, jQuery, SASS, MySQL, and Yoeman are skills that I know extremely well. In development are my skills in: Swift, Angular, OOP Javascript/PHP, Node.js, Java, and Ruby on rails. I know how to make use of API's, and how to share code as well as collaborate with other developers.

two_years.value: In the tech space building something fantastic that will turn heads. However still learning and staying on top of the latest trends and developments. The notion of "Sitting on a beach, earning 20%" sounds really boring to me. I'd rather build something awesome.

interests.value: I'm interested in this industry because nearly anything is possible with the enough passion and commitment. Ever since I was a kid I knew I wanted to be in the industry of James Bond gadgets and create something as cool as that.

why_attend.value: I love being on the leading edge of things. I have skills and experience that I know can help to create something fantastic. The only thing that has been missing is an opportunity to focus on the goal with some mentorship along the way. Thats why this program from UIT is that 1 in a million opportunity that you hear in rap songs.

anything_else.value: I believe that I am a smart, strong-willed, creative individual. I would very much appreciate the chance to try this new opportunity and to show myself exactly what I'm capable of.

code_experience.value: Up until the 7 hour course with Codecademy, I have had absolutely no experience with programming. I do love working with computers and I feel like it is something I could pick up fairly quickly.

two_years.value: In three years, I hope that I'll be in school studying and pursuing a career in business.

interests.value: I love business because everything has a structure. When you add in technology, especially since technology is always advancing, there's always new and exciting changes.

why_attend.value: I would like to attend UIT because business has been a huge part of my life. I've worked for a few different companies since graduating high school in 2011 but I'd love to learn more about business start up.

anything_else.value: My social media presence very much reflects my reality for the last several years. I find myself a trailing spouse in a depressed remote economy with no obvious role for me locally. Having left my previous career to follow my partner, I have been focused on growing food, raising children, and the problem of right livelihood for several years. Much of my blogging and micro-blogging is related to these questions. The advantages this brings me are at least two-fold. In the first place, I can bring highly developed soft skills to the program including self-knowledge, teamwork, and communication. I am a supportive and knowledgeable person who would be an asset to my classmates. Secondly, I have intimate knowledge of several growth niches that comprise ideal target markets for both B2C and B2B applications. (Local food, parenting, time management, and yoga/meditation immediately come to mind.) I am at a point of seeking a new challenge.Also, I will be remote camping w/o internet access from now until Aug 26.

code_experience.value: My programming experience is all pre-mobile. I worked on shopping carts and systems integration in the early 2000's, but shifted away from the code to online education content development around the time that CSS and XHTML were becoming the standards. This means that I have some scripting background but have only played with anything introduced since 2002 or so. I primarily worked with structured programming, but have found the shift to OOP fairly simple. I like code. I think like an engineer. I like the elegance of a solved problem. I expressed glee when I discovered how easy it was to make a circle in CSS/HTML these days. There's a certain amount of this that's a "coming home", to a world in which code is so much tidier and the platforms are so much more powerful.

two_years.value: I am convinced that we are all explorers. We can see what is in front of us, and we can make reasonable choices about where to go from here, but an awful lot can happen in three years to change our paths. I'm drawn to do more travel, teaching, and conferences. I would like to carry my experience into leadership roles and share the wealth of my background to help others achieve their own success. The precise form of that remains unclear.But what I can say is this: I've been working towards an integrated life for years. What remains unresolved is right livelihood. I am inspired by examples of people using new technologies to create novel solutions to the problem of earning a living while maintaining space for a whole life. If I do nothing, it's pretty clear it will just be more of the same: volunteer work, house maintenance, farming and blogging... which is lovely, but is getting boring. On the other hand, I can see that if I truly embrace online business, the potential surpasses my imagination

interests.value: I am no longer content to show up to support somebody else's vision of the world; I want to be part of the vision-holding. I see the world wide web becoming a web of support that makes people's lives easier to navigate from day to day. We've only just begun to scratch the surface of what's possible; Web 3.0 is going to be as different from our current experience as social media is from the static websites that preceded it, and I want to be a part of it.On a more concrete level, I see high-tech entrepreneurship as being part of the solution to long-term economic viability for the region. While our location is a challenge for many physical-world businesses, virtual services and products have no such inherent limitations. I'm concerned about the lack of primary economies, or over-reliance upon single revenue sources and would like to see diversification in our economy. And at a purely practical level, before I build things, I want to integrate strong business foundations (like a revenue model!) into my work.

why_attend.value: When I saw this, I thought, "That looks like great program." And after I considered it, I thought, "That looks like a great program *for me*." I have both professional and technical skills, but have found it challenging to pull them together into a focused project that generates revenue. I've been studying with the online business community, but I think that the environment of a cohort would provide exactly the sort of dynamic momentum I need to move from investigation and planning into building and implementation. In particular, I think that you can help me build capacity around the processes by which things move from idea to established business. These have always seemed more mysterious to me than the inner workings of my car. Yet I see that this program reframes the conceivability of start-ups... questions of partnerships and financing become problems and skills, which are thus solvable and learnable.

anything_else.value: I was once a part of a robotics team named Team-1114: Simbotics. In this, I learned not only how to work with my hands but the beginnings of coding and teamwork. While leaving in the last year, I made such an impression on one of the head mentors that he invited me to help him teach a grade 10 class in CAD software (another of my skills) during one of my spares.

code_experience.value: I spent my first 3 years of high-school in my school's "Computer Technology" class, a general computational class with programming aspects. On my 4th year, however, my teacher not only recommended me for the new "Computer Programming" course created that year, but pushed my forward into its Grade 12 version. From here I learned the ins-&-outs of Java, up to sorting algorithms and recursion, ending the course as my teacher's star student with a mark of 96%.

two_years.value: I see myself working on an idea to create an electricity storage device that can sell power produced by solar panels automatically to locations where price is determined by demand at the time. By using programs to time this device correctly, you could both support the environment and make a fair portion's worth of money. A proposal for such a device was sent to Mike Oulette last Thursday.

interests.value: Business is the art of manipulating cash-flow, but lacks knowledge in the field of digital development. Technology is the art of developing both civil and digital means of bettering other's lives, but lacks knowledge in how to profit in the process. Business AND technology together, however, is the ability to both better others' lives AND make a profit in the process to continue doing so. It is the possibility of doing just that that interests me the most.

why_attend.value: UIT is the only one of a limited set of institutions to offer training in both Technology and Business, two fields who's rise in demand is only matched by their lack of personnel. Furthermore, it is taught by an individual whom has shown prior success in the topic.

anything_else.value: I am self-motivated and very eager to learn!

code_experience.value: None.  While working at Volta I have realized that there are so many amazing opportunities both professionally and personally that I can take advantage of through learning/ applying code.

two_years.value: I really hate this question because I don't know the answer.  I know that I want to learn as much as I can and contribute back to society in the most necessary ways that I am skilled in.  I hope to be skilled enough in technology soon to be using it to make positive change soon.

interests.value: Business and Technology are two "givens" in today's society.  This means that in order to improve the current system, one must have to have a good grasp on both.

why_attend.value: UIT sounds like an amazing opportunity for those who did not have enough forethought in highschool to get a second chance at learning code from scratch with the advantage of immediately seeing/using its applications.

anything_else.value: I would ask you keep an open mind to older candidates with advanced degrees and lots of valuable work experience.  At first, while excited during the announcement about UIT I immediately felt it would focus on the youth. This demographic is an important segment but a homogenous class will not be the answer either.It was a young female that asked for my help with her application that got me to consider applying.  I told her how great I thought it was for her to apply and that I wish there was something like this when I was younger.  That conversation renewed my excitement in UIT and I applied.Finally, I consider myself a life-long learner. Ten years after my undergrad I went on to do a masters, I read 20 business books a year and currently I am studying Technology Entrepreneurship online.  I am a team player, problem solver, networker, entrepreneur and a strong candidate for your inaugural class.Regardless of the outcome of my application a sincere thank you for bringing this program to Cape Breton!

code_experience.value: My programming experience is hobbyist at best. I started with BASIC in the late 80’s, to C in the early 90’s and HTML around the same time.  My experience is often plagued with long breaks (1-2 years) and then trying to pick it up again.  This method has not worked so well because I am still not a proficient programmer in any language.I want to learn to code in an intensive environment because it would give me the ability to build and execute on an idea.  Combining my experience in usability with coding would result in a strong user experience skill set.  As a result of learning to code I would be able to teach others this important life skill.  As well, I would be able to join “hackathons” and make a meaningful contributions.Hence, my ability to learn code would be life changing for me and the people I help teach or mentor.  Adding this skill would allow me to remain in Cape Breton to help build the island’s next generation of companies, instead of traveling outside the region for work.

two_years.value: In 3 years, I envision myself still learning, failing and reiterating on my project whatever that may be.  While it would be nice to be celebrating my 1st exit, the reality is we have a lot of work to do to turn the economy around.I would like to think that as a result of all my hard work, in 3 years I would be in a position to mentor the burgeoning tech scene here in Cape Breton.  I am adaptable, outgoing, personable and like to help others, more important I like to learn by doing/teaching.  I have always wanted to establish an "idea cafe", incubator/coworking space in the downtown core.Inevitably, I do see myself involved with a "code camp" or afterschool program teaching kids, being part of UIT would help out a lot.  I would like to harness their creative abilities and focus that energy into building with code.  I am considering this for the fall of 2014. If the children are our future I want to make sure my son and his classmates are well prepared to be the future leaders of Cape Breton.

interests.value: The potential to transform entire economies is what excites me about business and technology.  Consider the farm lands of California transformed by a group of 8 people with an idea for a disruptive technology.  More recently the economic turnaround of Pittsburgh from a "steel city" to a technology hub. These are a few examples of the impact by changing community mindset from traditional industries to technology based. There is no reason this cannot happen here in Cape Breton.  Ever since I used my uncles' Commodore PET back in the 80's, to teaching myself HTML in the early 90's, I am fascinated with building.  In 1993, I built my 1st website for my program at DAL, nothing more than a collection of hyperlinks but it was amazing at the time.Ultimately, computer technology has the ability to transform and make something out of nothing, based on an idea.  Businesses built around that idea create value and solve problems.  I started my 1st business in 1996, my second in 2010 and I hope I am not finished yet.

why_attend.value: I want to attend UIT because of the opportunity it represents for me and my community.  UIT’s location has a real opportunity to invigorate the business community.  I feel the program provides the support and infrastructure required to launch a tech company.The opportunity to be part of something that has the potential to change the CB mindset is attractive. I feel the "startup" movement is the mechanism for change with the most potential to deliver.  Consulting for 18 years to a variety of industries and companies gives me a solid foundation to build upon. As a result, consider my age and global network as positive traits for my application. Overall, I am here to help rebuild the business community of the CBRM. My previous attempts to start communities should reflect on my passion for culture change. The immersive design of the program will provide a stimulating environment in which I feel I belong. UIT represents a hope for a better tomorrow and I would like to join this new group of entrepreneurs.

anything_else.value: I hope to stay entrepreneurial for my entire career. I have spent time in university, and I have spent time in an incubator. I am looking for a way to pursue my ideas while I learn, and being in a setting with peers and dedicated mentorship would be extremely helpful.

code_experience.value: I know some Web, Java and Matlab. I am currently building my web application and API called Layers. It is built with Node.js, Express.js, Mongodb, and Angular, Twitter Bootstrap, Fabric.js and I have defined JSON schemas, and implemented the CRUD endpoints for the database with tree structures (materialized paths). I am still developing the client-side for creation/viewing of a layer.

two_years.value: In three years I intend to have progressed my technical skills to such a degree that I can implement most of my ideas on my own, and will do so. I hope to be financially independent of my parents, and of education related debt.

interests.value: The modern internet is my favorite creation. I am fascinated by all of the data and content collected on the web, and how we interface with it. Business signifies more to me than just a way to make more money. Startups provide me a medium to build out my ideas, test their validity, and provide a product or service to the world that may never exist otherwise.

why_attend.value: Startups are very hard to do alone. It is very helpful for me personally to be around others when I work, both for encouragement and support. I spent time at Volta and learned much more working on things I was passionate about with colleagues building things. I find that many universities are too big and slow to keep up with technical innovation, and I think this is a step in the right direction.

code_experience.value: I've completed the HTML/CSS track on codeacademy, as well as dabbled in some Python and JavaScript in the past year or so. With Python I've mostly made small scripts for fun, like taking a base and exponent as raw input and spitting out the results. The main way I've been trying to learn JavaScript is by making a space shooter game you can check out on my github. It took a lot of googling and a lot of asking my comp-sci major friend but it's finally a bare bones game. (it actually started in Python with the PyGame library).

two_years.value: Hopefully using coding as at least a supplementary income.

interests.value: I've been interested in computers since I was a kid, and the fact that app-building/coding is becoming more accessible is super exciting to me. I love the idea of making something from scratch sitting at a computer and have it delivered to many different people all over the world.

why_attend.value: I want to attend UIT because for the last little while the idea of coding every day and eventually getting paid for it is becoming more and more appealing. The internet/computers aren't going anywhere and I think that UIT would provide me with the skills and experience necessary to seek employment in the field.

anything_else.value: I love performances, physical activity, and community involvement. I made 2 Halloween costumes and 1 Santa suit for Screech. Screech is a magnificent outlet for my energy and dance moves. I placed in 1 lip sync-and 2 business case competitions during my time at CBU; participated in 4 hair shows for Revive Hair Studio and dressed as a showgirl-twice-for Gord's Ride for the Cure. I was involved in the Savoy's rendition of Greece in 2011 and volunteered as mascot for the CB Dragon Boat Festival and Y12 lotto. I've been awarded top female snowboarded multiple times at Ski Ben Eoin-where I am a board member-and won 1st in my division at the JJ McDermott Half-Marathon-2014. I like rollerblading, trampolines, ATVs, and water sports. I served breakfast & dinner for Celtic Colors and helped a friend in Main A Dieu run for council in '12. I am on the organizing committee for the Be Emmazing Run/Walk-I ran with her the day she died. I want Emma's determination, honesty, and caring nature to be emulated across the world.

code_experience.value: I feel coding is a critical communication tool that will continue to grow in demand. Coding will provide me the framework to better express business proposals through story-telling, numbers and colors. I want to create a brand that promotes happy living, patience, forgiveness and tenacity. I'm good at creating visual appeal so coding skills will enable me create enticing virtual spaces people love to visit. I want a light hearted way to address serious issues like mental health, relationships, gratitude and forgiveness. I am a dynamic girl who likes to keep things fun but recognizes the severity of certain life conditions. My plan is to continuously generate enough money so I can employ and support projects and people I feel will benefit our world. I want to discover and create new ways to promote happy living through technology; apps designed to give daily inspiration and wisdom. Learning to code will prepare me for the increasingly fast-pace future of business and allow me to profit from past experiences.

two_years.value: I will be on the verge of 30, promoting physical activity and fine arts, inspiring others to learn to code and improve their vision of opportunity through technology. I will have completed 4/17 legs of the Cabot Trail Relay and be training for Boston. I would like to take part in a musical production, host a family dinner for 40+ guests, and begin planning a family of my own. I will organize a fundraiser for children through children's events; art, science, sport, literature, etc. My goal is to inspire all individuals to encourage themselves and others to strive for what they wish to experience by demonstrating a can-do attitude. I will remind myself that I am worthy of the wealth I've created here in Cape Breton and celebrate said success with the community through media and planned events. I hope to have gained great wisdom and appreciation for the people and opportunities presented to me while maintaining my youthful curiosity and compassion for others. Selling, donating, and reinventing my ideas :)

interests.value: How certain ideas or individuals simply have a much greater impact on the world than others. I am fascinated by the power of money and intrigued by the volume of information processed and stored via technology. I like how business and technology bring different skill sets and resources together, manifesting ideas to reality. I intend to build a career through fitness, fashion, family, community events and enthusiasm. Coding will allow me to communicate globally, connect with more people and grow. I like that there are virtually no limits in business or technology. I want to learn more from other people, cultures, and industries, while building a career that complements my lifestyle and satisfies my curiosity and competitive nature. I focus better when collaborating with people who engage passionately in goals. I studied accounting believing it to be the language of business; I see technology as a more prominent language and need to improve my skills to better succeed in business.

why_attend.value: I need help. Gratefully employed with my BBA since June 2010; I have worked in accounting, charity, retail, sales, food-services, promotions, and entertainment. I took no job lightly; managing orders at Belmac, collecting donations for the CBRHF, or shaking my tail feather as SCREECH for the CB Screaming Eagles; all experiences which will continue to serve me in the future. The diversity of my portfolio has made one thing obvious: technology is taking over. NOT-CODE:CODE = SINK:SWIM. I want to raise a family in Cape Breton with the notion that we are only limited by our imaginations. I imagine myself selling a happy living and feel coding is the framework I need to do so. Technology transmits infinite information instantly and brings people together quickly. I want focus on new projects that challenge youth in a positive way. I will use coding to express myself and bring the right people together to further promote mental health and physical activity.

anything_else.value: There's many things I'd like to convey to you that I don't think are distinguishable in 5120 characters but I hope that you get a sense of my excitement for the program and drive to use it as a means to grow and augment my community. I would be a mature student, but still in my mid-twenties. I have had some pretty interesting jobs I think I can pull experience from and understand the gravity that a program like this has on inspiring forward momentum in Cape Breton. I know that eyes will be on UIT  through it's first year, looking for it's successes and I think I would make a pretty positive and articulate graduate. I see my strengths in my soft-skills; being able to thoughtfully and emotionally convey a message to an audience and public speaking (skills learned through guiding), inspiring confidence in my team (through leadership training and team sports) and initiative (through self-managed work environments). I look forward to hearing from you.

code_experience.value: I have no programming experience, professionally or recreationally. I never anticipated this would be the reason I would be accepted into the UIT program, but hoped the application review committee would see the amount of work I have accomplished on code academy in such a short amount of time as an indicator of my willingness to learn and my passion for the subject material (I'm still trying to get my head around Java). To be honest, I didn't think I would like coding and started learning because it's languages seemed as useful as learning Mandarin, French or Arabic, but have found since I began that I find it quite therapeutic. The reason I would like to learn code is for the same reason I learned to do my own electrical, plumbing, and carpentry on my house. It's a tool to use to solve a problem. "I wonder if there's an app for _____? That app doesn't exist? I'll build it myself."

two_years.value: Short "big picture" answer: Working for myself, married to the love of my life, and in my backyard enjoying a bon-fire. Long, related answer: I can see myself fitting in to a couple of different streams, which I hope UIT will give me a diverse enough education to achieve.  I believe I have the creativity and confidence to head my own project, recruit founding partners and be one of the next success stories in Nova Scotia's emerging technology and creative based economy, but I can also see myself working with an existing tech oriented organization on new projects, or using my education to augment the activities of an organization in the arts and cultural sector.

interests.value: My interest in business stems from spending time with friends who have flourished as entrepreneurs as well as working for organizations that haven't ever really seemed to get it right, in my eyes. I've developed this fascination around how leadership can inspire and focus the skills and talents of it's team to meet a common end goal. I attended the Bachelor of Eco-tourism and Outdoor Leadership program at Mount Royal University and a business leadership course at CBU and learned that much of the same theory applies whether you're on a kayak expedition or launching a company. My interest in technology has been largely fostered by the concept that we can, as a global community, collaborate to solve the world's issues and still live where we want to live. I want to work with companies in Japan in my Sydney office, or Mabou if the weather is nice. A strong internet connection and a flexible business plan can allow me to do that. I've also been inspired by recent successes in Nova Scotia's tech sector.

why_attend.value: Seeing the potential for the tech sector to flourish in Cape Breton brings me hope that I made the right decision in trying to make a life for myself and my partner, here in Sydney. In my position as Social Engagement Liaison at the New Dawn Centre for Social Innovation, the projects I've been made aware of, and the organizations I've met with that have the most amount of energy and enthusiasm have undoubtedly been in the field of technology. I'm young and brash enough to jump on the bandwagon. I wish to learn a technical skill-set and hone my soft skills to create something no body else can do, on my island, for the world, on my terms.

anything_else.value: I am mature and don't mind working. I have experience of completing a self-directed project from my MScE. I continue managing the project as well, which is the development of an autonomous underwater robotic arm. I am responsible for the design and fabrication of the entire device. I have been with the project since its inception 4 years ago during my undergrad. All in all, I will be successful in the program. I enjoy working with people and I motivate them and push them to be their best. In turn it makes me work harder, I was always the underdog. I want to work with people who are passionate to shape and change the world. I want your mentorship. Thank you for your time.

code_experience.value: I have programmed a lot of numerical simulations for dynamic modelling and controller simulations. These were mainly completed in C (LabWindows CVI), MatLab, or Maple. I have a good understanding of indexing, reading/exporting data, etc. Also, I have used latex extensively including beamer presentations which has a similar structure to html although different syntax. Knowing tex certainly assisted with the Codecademy exercise. It was my first time writing html. I have also coded  simple Python and Fortran scripts merely as a tutorial. I believe learning c has helped adapt to new languages and syntax as it provides a foundation for understanding coding logic.

two_years.value: Working as a co-founder with an early start-up, preferably with an experienced CEO. For an initial start-up I believe there is greater value in working with a team with various strengths, having and experienced CEO and Board is essential. I will be a CEO on my second start-up.

interests.value: In short, everything. I was interested in pursuing the MTEI program and SMU following my MScE. However, a colleague who is a start-up co-founder in Fredericton suggested strong mentorship is more valuable after he completed various accelerator programs. When I saw this program, it excited me. Especially originally being from Cape Breton I believe it will be start-ups which grow our region. I love the idea of taking a dream and developing a product customers will actually want and benefit from. I also like the methodical approach to developing a product, analyzing the feed back, and refining it or pivoting. I like the Innovation associated with the two and how both areas require one another to thrive.

why_attend.value: Simply I just want to. I have this urge to do it. The best way to describe it is just brainstorming some of the reasons why I want to be there: I want the mentorship. I want to solve problems through innovation. I want to make an impact on society. I want to work with passionate people. I want to have fun and feel fulfilled, working to my maximum potential. I want to push life forward. I need the training you can offer. I have been interested in start-ups for a while. I have competed nationally for innovative engineering and won the Atlantic region's competition. I want to learn the skills to advance my technical knowledge into a sustainable business. I want to challenge myself. I want this opportunity.

anything_else.value: Just taking a look at the sign up process :)

code_experience.value: html/css, ruby, some python, some javascript, some objective-c.

two_years.value: Having fun creating new products, businesses, and tech.

interests.value: The art of developing technology & business.

why_attend.value: Learn lean methodologies to create awesome products and create businesses around them.

code_experience.value: Java, ruby (rails)

two_years.value: CEO of a series b company

interests.value: The ability to effect people lives, by making their lives easier and solving their problems. I really like what the internet has done, and it still the beginning.

why_attend.value: I want to learn about startups, get mentoring, and be around other entrepreneurs to bounce ideas with.

anything_else.value: UPDATE: My family bought our first home computer when I was 12. There was no internet, and I was told that it could only be used for typing. However, I discovered an early version of QuickTime. I figured out that adjusting the "resolution" to the lowest setting meant I could play about 6 seconds of the QuickTime demo clip. The computer would freeze, but I was proud to do something my parents said wasn't possible.In junior high, I quit band class because the non-band students got to take computer class. It was here that I discovered how to use a VPN to bypass the school filter to play online games. My favourite DOS game was a game-maker called ZZT. It was the first programming I'd ever done. My favourite book was "I Am David", so I made an entire map-based adventure game playing out the story of the book. Every character was programmed.In high school I took Java programming. I built an entire text-based BlackJack program during class time on my own.

code_experience.value: I've taken my first year of IT at NSCC Marconi Campus. Since then I have used my limited skills in Java to create programs for my own needs. I've also been teaching myself how to produce and DJ music. I've learned MIDI, music production software (Logic Pro X, Ableton), DJ software (Traktor), and visualization software (MixEmergency). Each of those programs are expensive, deep software that I continue to teach myself everyday. I also have been immersed in Twitter for the past year. I follow everyone I have an interest in (over 1000 at this time). I believe in the information-sharing power of Twitter and I absorb it by organizing everyone I follow into a collection of lists I created for interests I have. I use it everyday.

two_years.value: In 3 years I will have created something that people will enjoy. Whether it is hardware, software, music-related, or just an everyday app remains to be seen.

interests.value: The lines are grey between business and technology today. I have been pursuing interests in both since 2011. Here is a summary:Spring 2011 - Naively, quit my 3rd year of Commerce at Saint Mary's University with the goal of finding a "real" business job.Fall 2011 - Secured a job as a financial security advisor, despite the job requiring a degree.Spring 2012 - A huge financial opportunity came my way, but I was cut out because I wasn't comfortable with how we were getting clients. I quit the job and went to look for another way to make money.Fall 2012 - I was now splitting my time between scouting real estate, trading Forex via MetaTrader4, and exploring DJ software. All three I had taught myself.Spring 2013 - In spring I returned to university to give a business degree one last shot. But all I had learned in the past year had turned me to computers.Fall 2013 - I began IT at NSCC. I blew through my first year of IT, and I'm excited to continue learning.

why_attend.value: I have above average cognition. I can be taught one thing, and figure out the rest by asking questions. My ideal learning environment would be a fast-paced conversation with someone with experience, one-on-one with a notebook. I want to meet new people from whom I can learn. I've been to Hackathons at Heimdall in Sydney, and Volta in Halifax. Each time I attended, it has felt like home. But despite contributing original ideas, my lack of skills to develop them made me unable to lead the way. That's not who I believe myself to be. So I am in a juxtaposition where I know that I am a good leader and I have good ideas, but I also realize I'm often not the best choice to lead because of my skill set. It's not a lack of confidence, it's an honest self-assessment. But I'd like to change that about myself. I hope what I'm looking for is something I can get at UIT.

anything_else.value: I've really enjoyed my experience working at a tech startup and am now working to hone the skills necessary to be comfortable and capable as a founder. UIT looks like it has the potential to offer a kind of mentorship that is different from any bootcamp or incubator I've heard about to date. I'm interested to learn more about the UIT model and whether it might be a good fit.

code_experience.value: Intermediate HTML, CSS,  MySQL, Git. Entry level Ruby on Rails, Javascript. Can read/hack PHP (primarily in the context of Wordpress development). I've worked on a large scale SaaS product written in Ruby but not as a programmer.

two_years.value: In three years I'd like to have a couple of years experience going through the customer development process as a founder. Hopefully we'll have arrived at a repeatable and scalable model and we're into early customer creation.

interests.value: I think the act of creating solutions to business problems using technology is a fascinating and powerful process. I like the satisfaction of seeing an idea from problem to solution and the learning and creativity that happens along the way.

why_attend.value: After 3 years working in a customer support and product management role in a SaaS startup and 8 years overall experience in the web development space I am now focused on building my own startup. My initial focus has been working on strengthening my object oriented design, Ruby and Javascript skills and working through the Startup Owners Manual to freshen up on the customer development model. These self-directed learning elements are easy to do on my own, but UIT looks like it could help me with valuable mentorship in the soft skills I need to improve around pitching, raising money, team building, etc as well as providing fresh coding challenges.

anything_else.value: I've studied and worked in China, have been taking online courses from the University of Toronto while studying full time to earn my BBA and am eager to develop more skills that new starting businesses need. I would love to join UIT and help my home (Cape Breton) stand a chance of surviving today's changing economy.Just as another piece of information that may help you understand my personality, I strongly believe in taking action on discussions (especially those related to business). My personal website, thecolinpreneur.com, began as an experiment to learn web development and content management systems. Now I have turned it into a blog and an online platform for my digital marketing services. While developing my site has not been my top priority (currently working 40 hours a week and only able tackle my own projects in my free time) I do hope to develop it further and begin to earn a steady flow of work from it.

code_experience.value: I learned HTML in my first year at St.FX. During that time I was not interest in IT or computer science so I moved to focus in accounting and marketing. Now, I find myself buying books and how-to guides so I can build my own website (and perhaps 1 day, software). I have many ideas for businesses and am a doer.

two_years.value: In 3 years I would like to be experienced in business development & innovation so I could help others with their startups. I can see myself living in Cape Breton and having as much involvement as possible with developing Sandbox in Sydney/CBU. I currently work at Volta as an intern and would love to deliver the atmosphere and energy we have here to Cape Breton. Education-wise, I would like to have completed this program with UIT, write my GMAT and enter SMU's Masters of Technology, Enterprise, & Innovation. At that point I will move back to Cape Breton and help the economy with its restoration.

interests.value: When I was 12 years old I typed and sold my notes (making over $1,000). My grandfather (owner of 3 businesses) encouraged me to continue pursuing entrepreneurship and innovation. I attended St.FX and have a business degree. Now I am working for 2 startups (1 I am helping build and the other I am a part of the founding team) and am freelancing my own services (http://www.thecolinpreneur.com). Needless to say business and entrepreneurship runs in my blood. All of these startups require skills, leadership, and direction. I hope to gain those skills and lead those people.

why_attend.value: I want to attend UIT to learn the necessary technological skills I need to help grow and start businesses. I have been considering taking a 2-year program from NSCC in Information Technology but ultimately my goal is to be capable of directing and planning the tech process of application development for the web and mobile devices.

anything_else.value: I'm well on my way to my 1st Dan black belt (only 4 belts away) which I started 18 months ago. I hope this shows dedication and commitment and that given the opportunity I would see the course through to the end. Failing that don't make me have to use it ;-)

code_experience.value: Oodles of html 4.0, started as a Web developer (asp, java script and some php). These days I would look to learn ruby and or python. Would be good to understand hadoop for big data analysis. iOS and android though I would favour android for scope of available devices.

two_years.value: In 3 years time I would hope to have a few apps behind me. At least 1 killer. Open a couple of international offices. Be a UIT aluminium and using that experience  to teach others. I'd like to setup a space that enables businesses to collaborate together on shared problems and provide innovation. I'd like to have launched a managed Internet of things service and published my first book. I'd like to have been able to create opportunities for employment and help improve a number of communities with technology.

interests.value: I have a passion for it but I very much like to take technology and solve business problems but in a non standard way. Business could be so much easier if people used technology without putting in a specific box. Why can't a cloud orchestration engine control a connected building? Solving problems and puzzles interests me and with business and technology there are endless problems to solve and that means endless opportunities.

why_attend.value: I want to attend because it will harness the creative ideas I have and turn them into viable consumer and business based applications. Being technical yet business minded allows me to capture user needs exactly and deliver against them. My strong security background means I can also do this with a very secure approach, something I think is missing in the market today.

anything_else.value: I have been waiting for something like this to come along for a while. I have a huge amount of desire to succeed... I am a very driven person but I also understand I can be distracted when roadblocks arise and for me more than anything those roadblocks are technology related.Having a group of people to talk to, bounce ideas off, discuss problems and solutions and just support one another is what I need.I currently have 4 guys working for me from all over the planet and I would love to be in a position to help create jobs and growth here in Cape Breton.

code_experience.value: I have very little official programming experience. I didn't take any during high school but I did get some experience at McKenzie College working in Flash and Director.I have always been really good with math so after several years of waiting for our window & door supplier to provide a pricing program I build one in excel... this is my greatest programming achievement :) Here is a download link for the file for your own enjoyment. https://www.dropbox.com/s/3kr84t1d4kd22aj/Blank_Aug_22_2007.xlsI have recently purchased some programming courses on Udemy and planned to start them soon too.I want to learn to code because it is problem solving at its best... the solutions can be reused and recycled easily.

two_years.value: I see myself actively growing and expanding my app business with my children very involved in the vision and management. I want to be a leader in innovation and be a recognized leader in the mobile space.I have been thinking a lot lately about schools using apps to fundraise and this could be one solution to encouraging our youth to get involved with programming at an early age. Ideally I see myself working with kids (like mine) getting them excited about learning and being creative as they solve problems.

interests.value: I grew up in an entrepreneur household with my mom and dad; they have owned and operated several businesses every since I can remember. I have always been excited by recognizing a problem and working to create a solution.Technology is the great leveller! It has created an environment where someone without privilege or status can stand up and say "I have a solution" and not only be heard but change the lives of millions of people. That is EXCITING!!!!My wife and I were told "officially" recently that my oldest son has 2 learning disabilities. I know there are different learning types and I think smart technology can make it possible for learning to be super specific to the individual, learning based on the individuals responses, fine tuning the experience over time.

why_attend.value: I have been building a mobile game business over the last 3 years from home while working my full-time job. I finished my job in February and made the decision to focus on my app business full-time.I know the UIT environment is exactly what I need to take my vision and business to the next level. I know I will be a valuable student with experience, a willingness to work hard and participate fully with the group.

anything_else.value: I don't have the background in technology that most of your applicants will have, but I can learn. You won't find anyone else like me, I promise you that. I like to make people smile and think, And if I can get you to take a chance on me, I can promise you you won't be sorry.

code_experience.value: I've always wanted to learn code, but I never had the time to do it. I've started to see a certain beauty in code that I never noticed before. If I want to grow my own tech business, I know I need to learn code. I am just looking for the right teacher who can show me where to go next.

two_years.value: I want to be working for a young, vibrant company that is working towards keeping my generation employed and living in Nova Scotia. The added bonus would be if that business was my own creation.

interests.value: I've wanted to combine my passion for history with business and technology for some time. I believe my skill set with museums, public history, and photography/digital would work well with technology. I think that the next generation of artists and humanities majors will need to know a bit about business and technology to remain relevant. I want to be part of that wave.

why_attend.value: I've always had a bit of a soft spot for technology, but being an Arts student, I never had the time to pursue any kind of schooling in IT/computing. I would make a great addition to UIT because I am incredibly driven and want to expand my own knowledge base. I've got the tenacity, I just need someone to see that motivation in me and help me along the way.
